<section id="command-setheading">
<title>SETHEADING</title>
<indexterm><primary>SETHEADING</primary></indexterm>
<indexterm><primary>SETH</primary></indexterm>

<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term>Synopsis</term>
<listitem>
<synopsis><command>SETHEADING</command> <parameter>angle</parameter>
<command>SETH</command> <parameter>angle</parameter></synopsis>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Description</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Turns the turtle to a new absolute heading.
The <parameter>angle</parameter> input is the heading in degrees clockwise from the positive Y-axis.
In <link linkend="command-perspective">PERSPECTIVE</link> mode, the <parameter>angle</parameter> input is the heading in degrees from the positive X-Axis toward the positive Y-Axis rotating about the Z-Axis.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Example</term>
<listitem>
<programlisting><userinput>SETHEADING 45
SHOW HEADING</userinput>
45
</programlisting>

</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>See Also</term>
<listitem><simplelist>
<member><link linkend="command-heading">HEADING</link></member>
</simplelist></listitem>
</varlistentry>


</variablelist>
</section>
